<section class="section section--alt">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Dave Delaney 2026/2027 Keynote Presentations</p>
    <h2>The Communication Edge</h2>
    <p class="lede"><em>AI can write the email. It can't have the conversation.</em></p>
    <p>
      In an era when AI handles routine tasks, <strong>human communication is the competitive
      advantage</strong>. The Communication Edge helps leaders and teams cut through friction, have the
      conversations that matter, and communicate with the clarity, confidence, and impact that drives
      real results.
    </p>
    <p>
      As artificial intelligence takes over more of the routine work, the skills that remain distinctly
      human &mdash; trust, presence, difficult conversations, and genuine connection &mdash; are becoming
      the new competitive advantage. Teams retreat into silos. Hard conversations get replaced with
      polite agreement. Good intentions quietly create turnover, missed opportunities, and cultures
      where nobody says what they actually mean.
    </p>
    <p>
      In this high-energy, interactive keynote, Dave Delaney reveals the two words that change
      everything and teaches audiences the exact frameworks they'll use the moment they walk out the
      door.
    </p>
    <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--space-lg);">
      <p><strong>Time:</strong> 45&ndash;60 minutes</p>
      <p><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Company culture, leadership development, employee retention, sales teams, professional associations, and any organization navigating the future of work.</p>
      <p><strong>Optional add-on:</strong> The Communication Edge Workshop (90&ndash;180 minutes) as a breakout or half-day session.</p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Bonus:</strong> A free digital cheat sheet so attendees can revisit the key tools after the event.</p>
    </div>
    <details style="margin-top: var(--space-lg);">
      <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: 700; font-family: var(--font-display);">What audiences will learn&hellip;</summary>
      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-sm);">
        <p>
          Drawing on his original NICE, AND framework and the L.I.S.T.E.N. method, Dave shows audiences
          how to communicate more effectively across generations, departments, and roles in an
          increasingly AI-assisted workplace where human communication is no longer a soft skill. It's
          the edge.
        </p>
        <p><strong>Key Takeaways:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>A simple, immediately applicable language shift that replaces team friction with forward momentum</li>
          <li>The L.I.S.T.E.N. framework for becoming a more present, effective communicator in any conversation</li>
          <li>Practical tools for navigating difficult conversations, bridging silos, and building real trust</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>The ADHD Advantage</h2>
    <p class="lede"><em>Unlocking Strengths in Work and Life. Featuring The Root Down Framework.</em></p>
    <p>
      The ADHD Advantage, inspired by Dave Delaney's TEDx Talk, helps organizations recognize, support,
      and unlock neurodiverse strengths &mdash; featuring Dave Delaney's Root Down Framework: Know,
      Respect, and Connect Yourself.
    </p>
    <p>
      Most organizations have more untapped potential than they realize, and much of it lies in people
      who've spent their careers being told they're too much, not enough, or just wired wrong. Diagnosed
      with ADHD at fifty, Dave Delaney brings a funny, honest, and deeply human take on what ADHD
      actually looks like and what organizations gain when they stop managing neurodiversity and start
      unleashing it.
    </p>
    <div class="card" style="margin-top: var(--space-lg);">
      <p><strong>Time:</strong> 45&ndash;60 minutes (or customize for your agenda)</p>
      <p><strong>Ideal for:</strong> Leadership and professional development conferences, corporate retreats and off-sites, ERG and SIG programs, mental health and wellness events, universities and learning organizations.</p>
      <p style="margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Bonus:</strong> A simple take-home tool attendees can use to reinforce the Root Down Framework after the event.</p>
    </div>
    <details style="margin-top: var(--space-lg);">
      <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: 700; font-family: var(--font-display);">What audiences will learn&hellip;</summary>
      <div style="margin-top: var(--space-sm);">
        <p><strong>Key takeaways (Root Down Framework):</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Know Yourself:</strong> Identify your strengths and channel them into confidence and results</li>
          <li><strong>Respect Yourself:</strong> Build the self-acceptance that fuels resilience, reduces burnout, and unlocks growth</li>
          <li><strong>Connect Yourself:</strong> Practical strategies for reducing disconnection and building belonging at work and beyond</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

